section.article:
1. Each consignment of products referred to in Article 1 shall be accompanied by:
a report containing the results of sampling and analysis performed in accordance with the provisions of Commission Regulation (EC) No 401/2006 of 23 February 2006 laying down the methods of sampling and analysis for the official control of mycotoxins in foodstuffs,1 or with equivalent requirements, by a laboratory approved for that purpose by the Canadian Grain Commission;
a certificate in accordance with the model set out in the Annex, completed, verified and signed by a representative of the Canadian Grain Commission; the certificate shall be valid for four months from the date of issuance.
